      <h2>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now Terms of Service</h2>
      <p>Effective:  January 1, 2013<br>
                Last updated: April 29, 2013</p>
      <h3> <strong>PLEASE READ  THESE TERMS OF SERVICE CAREFULLY.</strong> </h3>
      <p>Your use of the Skin<sup>md</sup> Now website, app (application), chat, text, social media, including any use of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now by telephone, email, fax, is conditioned upon your acceptance of the Terms of Service. By using Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, you agree to be bound by the Terms of Service and any other agreements. If you, or any third party, do not agree to these Terms of Service, you are NOT authorized to access or use Skin<sup>md</sup> Now.</p>
      <h3> <strong>IMPORTANT  INFORMATION ABOUT YOUR USE OF THE ONLINE SERVICES</strong></h3>
      <p>DO NOT USE Skin<sup>md</sup> NOW FOR EMERGENCY MEDICAL NEEDS. If you experience a medical emergency, before or after using Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, call 911, or go to the nearest emergency room immediately. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now does not warrant any specific Turn-around Time -- time from when your request is submitted until when you receive a reply from a selected Provider (physician or non-physician health care professional).</p>
      <p>Services offered by Skin<sup>md</sup> Now are not intended to replace your relationship with your regular health care practitioners. Neither Skin<sup>md</sup> Now nor any of its contractors, licensors or suppliers shall be liable for any damages or losses related to any medical diagnosis, treatment or professional advice obtained from a Provider, nor for any damages or losses related to any other information obtained on Skin<sup>md</sup> Now.</p>
      <p>By using Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, user provides informed consent to Skin<sup>md</sup> Now and its Providers to use user’s health information for purposes of Treatment, Payment and Healthcare Operations.</p>
      <p>The content on Skin<sup>md</sup> Now should not be considered medical advice. You should always talk to a Provider or other appropriately qualified health care professional for diagnosis and treatment, including information regarding which drugs or treatment may be appropriate for you. None of the content from Skin<sup>md</sup> Now represents or warrants that any particular drug or treatment is safe, appropriate, or effective for you. Without limitation, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now does not recommend or endorse any specific tests, Providers, Consumer Advisors, medications, products or procedures.</p>
      <p>User is solely responsible for follow-up with a health care professional in a timely manner. </p>
      <h3><strong>HIPAA POLICY AND CONSENT FORM </strong></h3>
      <p>The Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) provides safeguards to protect your privacy. Implementation of HIPAA requirement officially began on April 14, 2003. Many of the policies have been our practice for years. This is an abbreviated version; however, the complete text is available on the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services web site: www.hhs.gov.</p>
      <p>HIPAA states that there are rules and restrictions on who may see or be notified of your Protected Health Information (PHI). These restrictions do not include the normal interchange of information necessary to provide you with medical services.</p>
      <p>User’s information will be kept confidential except as is necessary to provide services or to ensure that all administrative matters related to your care are handled appropriately. This specifically includes the sharing of information with other healthcare providers, laboratories, pharmacies, payment processors, scheduling staff and health insurance payers as is necessary and appropriate for your care.</p>
      <p>It is the policy of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now to update users of changes in their request’s status. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may do this by telephone, or e-mail, U.S. mail, or by any means convenient for Skin<sup>md</sup> Now and/or as requested by you. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may send user other communications informing you of changes to Skin<sup>md</sup> Now policy and new technology that user might find valuable or informative.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now agrees to provide users with access to their records in accordance with state and federal laws. User understands and agrees to inspections of and review of documents which may include PHI by government agencies or insurance payers in normal performance of their duties.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may change, add, delete or modify any of these provisions to better serve the needs of the Skin<sup>md</sup> Now and the user. User has the right to request restrictions in the use of your protected health information as the law permits. User’s confidential information will not be sold for any reason.</p>
      <p> User’s use of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will indicate that user has read the HIPAA information and consents to the guidelines set forth in the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act. </p>
      <h3><strong>PRIVACY POLICY </strong></h3>
      <strong>1. Introduction </strong>
      <p>This statement discloses the privacy policies and practices for the Online Services. Your use of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now indicates your acceptance of the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now is constantly innovating and implementing new features in its website to provide the best possible experience. This policy will continue to evolve as our website evolves.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now contains links to other sites. However, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such links. </p>
      <strong>2. Authorization, Consent and Acknowledgement </strong>
      <p>In order to participate in the Skin<sup>md</sup> Now Services, user will need to provide certain personal and medical information (PHI) about user either to Skin<sup>md</sup> Now or to a Provider without limitation, and providing Skin<sup>md</sup> Now directly with your name, e-mail address, mailing address, and phone number. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will share user’s PHI with Providers. Likewise, Providers will share user’s PHI with Skin<sup>md</sup> Now. </p>
      <p>By using Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, user consents to release of PHI.</p>
      <p>User may choose not to share PHI; however, user may not be able to utilize some features of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, including the Online Services furnished by Providers. All Providers have represented to Skin<sup>md</sup> Now that they will comply with all federal and state privacy and security laws applicable to user’s interactions with such Providers. However, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now is not responsible for any violations of those laws by individual Providers.</p>
      <p>If you are a user who is submitting information that is the PHI of another person, user acknowledges that he/she has obtained informed consent of this other person prior to such a submission of PHI.</p>
      <p> Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may obtain personal data from your health plan, laboratory, pharmacy, pharmacy benefits manager and other third parties. That data will be subject to the same privacy and security policies as the PHI that you submit to us.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will not share your PHI with any other third parties without your express permission, except as otherwise permitted by these Terms of Service or as required by law or a court.</p>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will use your email address as the primary means to reset your username and password. Your email address must not be shared with any other third party. On occasion, we may contact you to inform you of product improvements, assess consumer satisfaction, or solicit your feedback for continuous improvement of our Online Services, and for similar reasons. From time to time, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may combine, in a non-identifiable format, some of the PHI you provide with information from others to create aggregate reports. This type of information is essential for us to operate and identify ways to improve our services and may also be used for general public health purposes. Aggregate data does not contain any information that could be used to contact or identify you.</p>
      <p>The data Skin<sup>md</sup> Now collects via the Skin<sup>md</sup> Now website is audited internally. It also helps Skin<sup>md</sup> Now troubleshoot a problem for user and/or Provider. This information is accessed only by authorized Skin<sup>md</sup> Now representatives.</p>
      <p>By using Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, user authorizes the use of photographs or pathology slides for medical research, education, science, insurance providers or marketing. Safeguards will be taken to maintain patient confidentiality and patient identity. However, in certain, limited, circumstances, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may use and disclose user’s PHI without consent or authorization if Skin<sup>md</sup> Now obtains approval through a special process to ensure that such research poses little risk to your privacy. In any case, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now would never allow researchers to use your name or identity publicly. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now may also release user’s health information without user’s written authorization to people who are preparing for a future research project, so long as no personally identifiable information is disclosed.</p>
      <p>If user would like to delete or modify user’s PHI, please contact Customer Support at info@skinmdnow.com. User has the right to ask that Skin<sup>md</sup> Now limit how it uses and discloses user’s PHI. Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will consider user’s request, but are not legally required to accept it. If Skin<sup>md</sup> Now accepts user’s request, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now will put any limits in writing and abide by them except in emergency situations. User may not limit the uses and disclosures that Skin<sup>md</sup> Now is legally required or allowed to make.</p>
      <p>This authorization will expire when user revokes it in writing. User has the right to revoke this authorization in writing except as Skin<sup>md</sup> Now has acted in reliance upon this authorization. User’s written revocation must be submitted to: info@skinmdnow.com </p>
      <h3>WAIVER FOR NON-COVERED SERVICES / ADVANCE BENEFICIARY NOTICE OF NONCOVERAGE</h3>
      <p>By using the services of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now, user acknowledges that Skin<sup>md</sup> Now’s services are not covered by your healthcare insurance, and user’s healthcare insurance will not be billed for such services. User agrees voluntarily, and under no duress, to be responsible for any fees incurred from user’s use of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now services.</p>
      <h3>ACCURACY AND COMPLETENESS OF INFORMATION </h3>
      <p>You, the User, are solely responsible for ensuring that information provided to Skin<sup>md</sup> Now is both accurate and complete. You acknowledge that information accuracy and completeness are critical for the efficient and legal provision of Skin<sup>md</sup> Now services. Covered information includes, but is not limited to, name, gender, date of birth, state of residence, billing information, phone number, drug allergies, personal and family medical, pharmacy information, and any information, or photographs, related to Condition (reason for submitting request).</p>
      <h3><strong>AVAILABLE PROVIDERS</strong></h3>
      <p>User may select a Provider based on specialty, location and/or fee. User must be a resident of the state or physically present in the state, in which the user-selected Provider is licensed to practice. Providers are independent (i.e., not employed by, or under contract to, Skin<sup>md</sup> Now to provide services on its behalf).</p>
      <h3><strong>SELECTING A PROVIDER</strong></h3>
      <p>Skin<sup>md</sup> Now does not make any representations or warranties about the Providers’ training or skill.</p>
